problem:
Rhombus $ABCD$ is similar to rhombus $BFDE$. The area of rhombus $ABCD$ is 522, and $\angle BAD=60^\circ$. What is the area of rhombus $BFDE$?

[asy]
pair A,B,C,D,I,F;
A=(0,0);
B=(10,0);
C=(15,8.7);
D=(5,8.7);
I=(5,2.88);
F=(10,5.82);
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(D--I--B--F--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$E$",I,W);
label("$F$",F,E);
[/asy]
